Description: Body sherd of small Attic black-figured pottery open vase, perhaps a skyphos; interior glazed black; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of part of naked man running right.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 441, no. B723)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0347) (Phase 1)
